<title>USA: Trigen sees gain from early debt payment.</title>
<headline>Trigen sees gain from early debt payment.</headline>
<dateline>WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. 1996-10-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Trigen Energy Corp said Monday it prepaid $7 million in subordinated debt, which will boost after-tax earnings per share by $0.02 over the next year.</p>
<p>Trigen prepaid the debt by issuing 200,000 shares of Trigen to the lender and selling 240,000 shares to Trigen's parent company, Elyo.</p>
<p>In repaying this debt, Trigen said, it incurred about $3.0 million in costs, about $1.8 million net of income taxes, which will be accounted for as an extraordinary loss.</p>
<p>This loss will be offset by a gain from a recent condemnation award, it said.</p>
<p>Trigen owns and operates community energy systems and co-generation facilities.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610</p>
